### Describe your change:
This PR introduces a novel, probabilistic sorting algorithm called **Half-Life Sort** (`half_life_sort.py`).

It is inspired by the physics of radioactive isotope decay. Instead of deterministically swapping out-of-order elements (like Bubble Sort), it iterates through the array and gives every out-of-order adjacent pair (an "inversion") a 50% probability of "decaying" (swapping) into a stable, sorted state. The algorithm loops over the collection until it reaches perfect stability.

While theoretically highly inefficient, it mathematically guarantees a sorted array eventually and serves as a unique educational demonstration of probabilistic time complexity and non-deterministic algorithms.

